## Why This Is Asked
This question evaluates a candidate's ability to design a practical, end-to-end DevOps pipeline that integrates CI/CD, containerization, environment management, and quality gates.

## Key Concepts
- Azure DevOps YAML pipeline configuration
- Maven test lifecycle and build process
- Docker image building and ACR registry management
- Azure App Service deployment slots and slot swapping
- Performance testing with k6 load testing tool
- Manual approval gates and automated rollback strategies

## Code Example
```javascript
import http from 'k6/http';
import { check, sleep } from 'k6';

export let options = {
  thresholds: {
    http_req_duration: ['p(95)<500'],
    http_req_failed: ['rate<0.01']
  }
};

export default function() {
  let health = http.get('https://staging-app.azurewebsites.net/health');
  let metrics = http.get('https://staging-app.azurewebsites.net/metrics');

  check(health, {
    'health status is 200': (r) => r.status === 200
  });

  check(metrics, {
    'metrics status is 200': (r) => r.status === 200
  });

  sleep(1);
}
```

## Why This Is Asked
This question evaluates expertise in multi-tenant GitOps workflows spanning multiple clusters, secure secret management, and production-grade cost controls.

## Key Concepts
- GitOps for multi-tenant, multi-cluster deployments
- Per-tenant namespace isolation and resource management
- Azure Key Vault integration with managed identities for secure secret handling
- ArgoCD App of Apps pattern for scalable tenant manifest management
- Istio canary deployments with traffic shaping and comprehensive health monitoring
- Approval workflows, automated rollback mechanisms, and cost budget enforcement

## Code Example
```javascript
// Example: fetch a Key Vault secret via Azure SDK (JS)
const { DefaultAzureCredential } = require("@azure/identity");
const { SecretClient } = require("@azure/keyvault-secrets");

const credential = new DefaultAzureCredential();
const client = new SecretClient(keyVaultUrl, credential);
const secret = await client.getSecret(secretName);
```

## Why This Is Asked
This question evaluates your ability to orchestrate complex multi-namespace deployments in AKS using Helm, Istio, and policy-based gates. It tests your understanding of rollback mechanisms and drift handling, while demonstrating concrete implementation steps, risk assessment capabilities, and production-readiness practices.

## Key Concepts
- Azure DevOps pipeline orchestration
- Helm upgrades with environment-specific values
- Istio canary traffic routing strategies
- Azure Key Vault integration for secrets management
- Kubernetes drift detection using kubectl diff
- Policy-based deployment gates and automated rollback

## Code Example
```javascript
// Example health check for deployment validation
async function isHealthy(pod) {
  try {
    const response = await fetch(`http://${pod}/health`);
    return response.status === 200;
  } catch (error) {
    console.error(`Health check failed for pod ${pod}:`, error);
    return false;
  }
}
```
